xt-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The benefits of providing opportunities and services to people with disability by far out</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">weigh the costs. Rehabilitating a young man with spinal injury can </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">directly benefit the entire family. Rehabilitation can prevent poverty within the household and ensure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> for example</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that children go to school.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="45" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">In relation to the issue of the UK’s work with other development agencies and partner governments on disabilit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">y:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="46" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Many of the activities outlined under sub</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">paragraphs in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rticle 32 are expected to be achieved through government collaboration with a range of actors, including organizations representing persons with disabilities, intergovernmental organizations and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">other international development actors</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">8</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="47" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">In relation to the issue of the UK’s role in ensuring post-2015 development goals consider disability issues:</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="48" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Disability is currently excluded from the current MD</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">G'</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s. Work is in progress to address this in the pos</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t-2015 development environment, including through the 2013 High Level Meeting on Disability and Development that was held in Sept 2013. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">fID's active involvement in this process can help shape the post 2015 MDG's and in turn help shape  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">its own </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">international development programme that is more inclusive of disability issues.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#